  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HCFC phase-out management plan (stage I)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HCFC Phase-Out Management Plan (Stage I) The Government is proposing to follow the Montreal Protocol schedule and adopt a staged approach to achieve the complete phase-out of HCFCs by 2030 with a service tail to 2040. The current submission only consists of stage I of the HPMP to achieve a 35 per cent reduction by 2020, and focuses largely on activities for the servicing sector using HCFC-22.  Description of Activities Training of customs officers and other law enforcement personnel (UNEP) Training of technicians on good practice, recovery, reuse and retrofit, handling of natural refrigerants (UNEP) Provision of tools and equipment for recovery, reuse and retrofit, refrigerant identifiers (UNIDO) Technical support to servicing workshops and retrofit centres, demonstration of retrofit and safe handling of hydrocarbon refrigerants (UNIDO) Monitoring, coordination and reporting (UNEP)</narrative>
  </description>
